===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*h₂er-}}
From (1386) {{inh|en|enm|armee}}, borrowed from {{der|en|fro|armee}} (cf. modern French {{m|fr|armée}}), from {{der|en|ML.|armāta||armed force}}, a noun taken from the past participle of {{der|en|la|armāre||to [[arm]]}}, itself related to {{m|la|arma||tools, arms}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₂er-||to join, fit together}}.
{{doublet|en|armada}}. Displaced native {{noncog|enm|heere}}, {{m|enm|here}}, from {{noncog|ang|here}}.

